headline: Things Are Getting Weird for EVs After Trump’s Win
summary: President-elect Donald Trump, who’s headed back to the White House, is likely to roll back some vehicle emissions rules and electric vehicle policies during his term in the Oval Office.  Just how far he will go—and is allowed to—is hard to say, especially as Trump continues to court the support of the the world’s richest man and Tesla CEO Elon Musk.  Trump will also likely loosen EPA emissions standards, which Republicans have recently referred to as EV “mandates.”
